#8281
Tutorial: Movement and Looking~
Getting around in Project Twilight is straightforward. You move using
\tCnorth\tn, \tCsouth\tn, \tCeast\tn, \tCwest\tn, \tCup\tn, and
\tCdown\tn (or just \tCn\tn, \tCs\tn, \tCe\tn, \tCw\tn, \tCu\tn,
\tCd\tn).

The \tClook\tn command shows you the current room. You can also
\tClook\tn at objects, people, or specific keywords in the room
description. The \tCexits\tn command shows available exits.

Try '\tWlook\tn' to refresh the room, '\tWexits\tn' to see exits,
then go \tWnorth\tn.
~
0 8 0
E
XNUMB1~
Unnamed Room~
E
XDUMB1~
None~
E
north~
Type 'north' or just 'n' to move north. Other directions: south (s), east (e), west (w), up (u), down (d).~
E
exits~
Syntax: exits - Shows a detailed list of available exits from the current room. The auto-exit display in brackets (e.g., [Exits: north south]) shows a compact version automatically when you enter a room.~
E
look~
Syntax: look - Shows the current room description, objects, and people. Syntax: look <target> - Look at an object, person, or keyword. Syntax: look in <container> - Look inside a container. The look command is your primary way of observing the world around you.~
