#8283
Tutorial: Roleplaying~
Roleplaying is the heart of Project Twilight. Here are the tools
to help you get into character:

  \tCdescription\tn - Set what others see when they look at you
  \tCnature\tn \tW<archetype>\tn - Your inner personality
  \tCdemeanor\tn \tW<archetype>\tn - How you appear to others
  \tCrpavailable\tn \tW[message]\tn - Mark yourself as looking for RP
  \tCrpwho\tn / \tCwhorp\tn - See who is available for RP
  \tCrpjoin\tn \tW<name>\tn - Travel to an available player
  \tCrpmode\tn - Toggle RP mode (no hunger/thirst interruptions)

Try '\tWdescription\tn' to set how your character looks, then go
\tWnorth\tn.
~
0 8 0
E
XNUMB1~
Unnamed Room~
E
XDUMB1~
None~
E
rpwho~
Syntax: rpwho (or whorp) - Shows a list of players who are currently available for roleplaying, along with any message they have set about what they are looking for.~
E
rpmode~
Syntax: rpmode - Toggles RP mode on and off. In RP mode, you are freed from hunger, thirst, and other out-of-character interruptions so you can focus on your scene.~
E
rpavailable~
Syntax: rpavailable [optional message] - Makes you visible on the RP-available list. Other players can see you with 'rpwho' or 'whorp' and travel to you with 'rpjoin'. Set a message describing what kind of RP you are looking for.~
E
demeanor~
Syntax: demeanor <archetype> - Sets how your character appears to others. Your demeanor is the face you show the world. It can change more easily than your nature. See 'help archetypes' for a list.~
E
nature~
Syntax: nature <archetype> - Sets your character's inner personality. Your nature is who you truly are inside, which may differ from how you present yourself. See 'help archetypes' for a list of available personality types.~
E
description~
Syntax: description (no arguments) - Opens the text editor to write your character's physical description. This is what others see when they look at you. Include details like build, hair, eyes, clothing style, and demeanor. Type your description, then type '@' on a blank line to finish.~
