E
job~
Syntax: job commands - Lists available job commands. Syntax: job apply <employer> <profession> - Apply for a job. Jobs provide income and experience. You need job energy to perform work tasks, which regenerates over time while resting or sleeping.~
E
trade~
Syntax: trade buy <shares> <company> - Buy stock shares. Syntax: trade sell <shares> <company> - Sell stock shares. You must be at a bank to trade stocks.~
E
stocks~
Syntax: stocks - Displays the current stock market with ticker symbols, prices, trends, and your portfolio value. You can buy and sell stocks at any bank using the 'trade' command.~
E
sell~
Syntax: sell <item> [keeper] - Sells an item from your inventory to a shopkeeper. Not all shops buy all types of items.~
E
buy~
Syntax: buy <item> [keeper] - Purchases an item from a shopkeeper. The cost is deducted from your cash on hand.~
E
list~
Syntax: list [keeper] - Shows what a shopkeeper has for sale, including prices and wear locations.~
