#8286
Tutorial: The World Around You~
Bal Harbor is a living city with systems to explore:

  \tCtime\tn - See the current date and time
  \tCscore\tn - View your full character sheet
  \tCresearch list\tn - See available research topics
  \tCresearch\tn \tW<topic>\tn - Research lore and history
  \tCread\tn - Read a newspaper (if you are holding one)
  \tCstep\tn - Travel quickly between known locations
  \tCtaxi\tn - Hail a taxi to various destinations

The city has newspapers, a stock market, a research library, and
an influence system that lets you affect the world around you.

Try '\tWtime\tn' to see the clock, then go \tWnorth\tn.
~
0 8 0
E
XNUMB1~
Unnamed Room~
E
XDUMB1~
None~
E
influences~
The influence system lets you exert power over the city through Political, Media, Church, Economic, Police, and other channels. Type 'help influences' for details on how to build and use influence.~
E
taxi~
Syntax: taxi - Shows a list of taxi destinations. Syntax: taxi <location> - Takes a taxi to that destination. Taxis cost money but can take you to additional locations beyond the step list.~
E
step~
Syntax: step - Shows a list of locations you can travel to. Syntax: step <location> - Teleports you to that location. The step command is a convenient way to travel between known areas quickly.~
E
newspaper~
You can buy newspapers from newsstand vendors around the city. Once you have one, type 'read' to see the front page, or 'read <number>' to read a specific article.~
E
research~
Syntax: research list - Shows available research topics. Syntax: research <topic> - Attempt to research a topic using your Intelligence and relevant abilities. Success reveals lore and in-character information. There is a 24-hour cooldown between attempts on the same topic.~
E
time~
Syntax: time - Displays the current in-game date and time, as well as the real server time. The game runs at 60x real time (1 real minute = 1 in-game hour).~
