#8287
Tutorial: Combat~
Project Twilight uses a \tCcombo-based combat system\tn rather than
simple "kill" commands. Combat moves can be chained together:

  \tBStrike Moves:\tn \tClblow\tn, \tCrblow\tn, \tCkick\tn,
    \tCskick\tn, \tCbite\tn
  \tBGrab Moves:\tn \tClgrab\tn, \tCrgrab\tn
  \tBDefense:\tn \tClblock\tn, \tCrblock\tn, \tCfblock\tn
  \tBMovement:\tn \tCcflip\tn, \tCcroll\tn, \tCcjump\tn,
    \tCspin\tn, \tCsweep\tn
  \tBControl:\tn \tCcstop\tn (stop fighting), \tCcstand\tn (rebalance)

\tYNote:\tn Most conflicts in Project Twilight are resolved through
roleplay rather than the combat system. Combat is a tool, not the
primary gameplay.

Type '\tWhelp combat\tn' for full details, then go \tWnorth\tn.
~
