#8288
Tutorial: Character Growth~
Your character grows by spending \tCexperience points\tn (XP):

  \tCscore\tn - View your full character sheet
  \tCtrain\tn - Spend XP to raise attributes and abilities
  \tCadvance\tn - Spend XP to raise supernatural powers
  \tCcostcalc\tn \tW<attribute>\tn - Check how much a raise costs

You earn experience through roleplaying with other players,
performing job functions, and exploring the world. Type '\tWscore\tn'
to see your current stats.

When you are ready, go \tWnorth\tn to learn about the playable
races.
~
0 8 0
E
XNUMB1~
Unnamed Room~
E
XDUMB1~
None~
E
experience~
Experience points (XP) are earned through roleplaying, jobs, and other activities. Spend them with 'train' (for attributes and abilities) or 'advance' (for supernatural powers). Type 'costcalc <stat>' to check costs.~
E
advance~
Syntax: advance - Shows what supernatural powers you can improve. Syntax: advance <power> - Spends experience to raise a power. Vampires advance disciplines, werewolves advance gifts.~
E
train~
Syntax: train - Shows what attributes and abilities you can improve. Syntax: train <category> <attribute> - Spends experience to raise an attribute or ability. Use 'costcalc' to check costs before spending.~
E
score~
Syntax: score - Displays your full character sheet including attributes, abilities, health, experience, and other vital statistics.~
