#8292
Tutorial: Vampires~
\tBThe Kindred\tn are the undead, cursed descendants of Caine.
They survive on \tCblood\tn and wield ancient \tCdisciplines\tn.

Key vampire commands:
  \tCfeed\tn - Feed on a mortal to replenish blood
  \tCblood\tn - Check your current blood pool
  \tCfangs\tn - Bare your fangs
  \tCdisciplines\tn (or \tCdiscs\tn) - View your vampire powers
  \tCregen\tn - Spend blood to heal wounds

The seven Camarilla clans:
  \tWBrujah\tn - Passionate rebels and fighters
  \tWGangrel\tn - Feral loners close to the Beast
  \tWMalkavian\tn - Mad seers cursed with insight
  \tWNosferatu\tn - Monstrous spies of the sewers
  \tWToreador\tn - Artistic hedonists and socialites
  \tWTremere\tn - Secretive blood sorcerers
  \tWVentrue\tn - Aristocratic rulers of the Camarilla

Beware of \tCtorpor\tn - if your blood runs dry, you fall into
a deathlike sleep.

Go \tWnorth\tn to continue to the exit.
~
0 8 0
E
XNUMB1~
Unnamed Room~
E
XDUMB1~
None~
E
regen~
Syntax: regen - Spend blood to heal your wounds. Vampires can recover from injuries that would kill a mortal by expending vitae.~
E
feed~
Syntax: feed <target> - Attempt to feed on a mortal to replenish your blood pool. Feeding is a core mechanic of vampire existence.~
E
torpor~
Torpor is the deathlike sleep that claims a vampire when their blood pool is depleted. A vampire in torpor is helpless and vulnerable. Keep your blood pool replenished to avoid this fate.~
E
fangs~
Syntax: fangs - Bares your fangs. A subtle intimidation tool during roleplay, revealing your true nature.~
E
disciplines~
Syntax: disciplines (or discs, powers) - View your vampire powers and their levels. Each clan has three primary disciplines, but vampires may learn others. Advance them with experience using the 'advance' command.~
E
blood~
Vampires sustain themselves on blood. Your blood pool fuels your disciplines and keeps you from falling into torpor. Use 'feed' on mortals to replenish, and 'blood' to check your current level.~
